==English==
=== Etymology ===
From Spanish ''el lagarto'', "the lizard".

===Noun===
#large reptile with sharp teeth and very strong jaws related to the [[crocodile]] and are native to the Americas and China.
#:''All you could see of the alligator were its two eyes above the water, and suddenly it snatched up and caught the poor bird with its strong jaws full of sharp teeth''.

